---
title: "MODULAR — config-driven BRANCH: standard for_each loop + separate LME workstream"
---
flowchart TD
  classDef cond fill:#FDEBD0,stroke:#B9770E,color:#7E5109,font-weight:bold;
  classDef nb fill:#E8F6F3,stroke:#148F77,color:#0E6251;
  classDef leaf fill:#FEF9E7,stroke:#B7950B,color:#7D6608;
  classDef ctrl fill:#EBF5FB,stroke:#2E86C1,color:#1B4F72,font-weight:bold;

  CFG["study_config_modular<br/><i>model_family = standard | lme</i>"]:::ctrl --> LC
  LC["load_config_branched<br/><i>split into standard[] and lme[]</i>"]:::ctrl --> BS{{"branch:<br/>has_standard?"}}:::cond
  LC --> BL{{"branch:<br/>has_lme?"}}:::cond

  %% ---- Branch 1: standard family, shared for_each loop ----
  BS -->|true| FES["for_each(standard studies)<br/>concurrency = 4"]:::ctrl
  subgraph RS["run_study_modular  (shared standard pipeline)"]
    direction LR
    F["dispatch_feature"]:::nb --> Q{{"quality_gate"}}:::cond
    Q -->|pass| M["dispatch_matching"]:::nb --> MD["dispatch_model"]:::nb --> I["insights"]:::nb
  end
  FES --> F
  MD -. "runs the config-named leaf" .-> SL["feature_standard / matching_standard /<br/>matching_stratified / model_att / model_did"]:::leaf

  %% ---- Branch 2: LME family, its OWN separate workstream ----
  BL -->|true| FEL["for_each(lme studies)<br/>concurrency = 4"]:::ctrl
  subgraph RL["run_lme_study  (DEDICATED LME workstream — its own notebooks)"]
    direction LR
    LF["feature_lme"]:::leaf --> LQ{{"quality_gate"}}:::cond
    LQ -->|pass| LM["matching_lme"]:::leaf --> LMD["model_lme"]:::leaf --> LI["insights"]:::nb
  end
  FEL --> LF

  N["The config DECIDES, then the flow BRANCHES. Standard models (ATT/ATE/DID/pre-post) share<br/>one pipeline and fan out with for_each. LME is structurally different (multi performance period),<br/>so it breaks off into its OWN workstream with its OWN notebooks and can diverge freely.<br/>Add another odd-shaped model = another branch + workstream. Add a standard model = a leaf + a config row."]:::ctrl
